%description:
If document has DTD, parser must use it for validation and attribute completion.
Document doesn't conform to DTD: extra element -- should be an error.

THIS TEST DOES NOT PASS WITH EXPAT -- IT DOES NOT SUPPORT DTD VALIDATION.

%file: test.dtd
<!ELEMENT foo ( bar )>
<!ATTLIST foo
            one      CDATA "F1"
>

<!ELEMENT bar EMPTY>
<!ATTLIST bar
            one      CDATA "B1"
            two      CDATA "B2"
>

%file: test.xml
<?xml version="1.0" ?>
<!DOCTYPE foo SYSTEM "./test.dtd">
<foo>
    <bar one="X"/>
    <extraElem/>
</foo>

%activity:
cXMLElement *node = getEnvir()->getXMLDocument("test.xml");
EV << node->getXML();

%exitcode: 1

%contains-regex: stderr
Cannot load 'test.xml': No declaration for element extraElem

